<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7918764>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Salvia cajamarcana. A Inflorescence with upper portion of flowering branch. B Flower. C Calyx. D Corolla. E Ventral corolla dissection showing the stamens and the style (lower lip previously removed) (photographs from Oxamarca, District Oxamarca, Province Celendín, Department Cajamarca, by M. Roncal-Rabanal, corresponding to the type collection)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7918764/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7918766>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Color variation in the flowers of Salvia cajamarcana. Calyces with dense whitish (A) or ferruginous pubescence (B & C), or the hairs not so dense such the green calyx surface is visible (D). Corolla dark blue to purple (A, B & D) or lilac (C) (A & C from Lluchubamba, District Sitachocha, B & D from Oxamarca, District Oxamarca; photographs by R. Uría)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7918766/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7918760>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Maps showing the geographical distribution of Salvia cajamarcana (white triangles) and S. revoluta (white dots). In the main map, Peru is highlighted with a more intense background; the inset shows the area occupied by both species. Political boundaries of Peruvian Departments are shown (background of the maps taken from Google Earth Pro 7.3.48642)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7918760/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7918762>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Habitat of different populations of Salvia cajamarcana (A–C) and S. revoluta (D), all in the Department Cajamarca.A Laguna San Nicolás, District Namora, Province Cajamarca. B Lluchubamba, District Sitacocha, Province Cajabamba. C Oxamarca, District Oxamarca, Province Celendín. D Callampampa, District Llama, Province Chota (photographs by R. Uría and F. Lozano)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7918762/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7918758>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Salvia revoluta. A Inflorescence. B Flower. C Calyx. D Corolla. E Ventral corolla dissection showing the stamens and the style (photographs from R. Uría’s private garden in Mar de Plata, Buenos Aires Province,Argentina, originally collected at Callampampa, District Llama, Province Chota, Department Ancash, Perú by R. Uría)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7918758/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

